We have a kraken Motor with a talon FX motor controllers that we are trying to configure for the first time. The talon is flashing red (as expected) and everything else on the CAN bus upstream and downstream of the talon works as expected. When we connect to our roborio, I can see our pigeom IMU fine, but the talon does not show up at all. At one point (after asking another team for help), the talon showed up in Phoenix tuner but was grayed out and unable to be clicked or modified. Any suggestions for troubleshooting steps or possible causes?

ConnorMasini:

The talon is flashing red (as expected)

That is not expected. As is documented in the Status Light Reference, that means the device does not see the CAN bus, which typically means there’s a wiring issue. See CAN Bus Troubleshooting.

Hmm apparently the Google AI summary lied about that. It said it just meant it wasn’t configured yet. However , I don’t see how it could possibly be a CAN issue. We have it in wired in the middle of our swerve modules which all still drive and turn as they should (and our pigeon IMU still works as well). Wouldn’t a CAN issue take down everything on the bus, not just the single new controller added in?

That’s a good idea. I set some newer students off to put it together without supervision and they may not have put it together correctly. They definitely had the correct screws (they only had the box that the kraken came in), but it wouldn’t completely surprise me if a wire was loose. If the CAN connectors for the Talon are loopback connectors that would completely explain the issue. Thanks
